(5201, '613CB070-D879-42BE-B67F-435734555280', 'Hey love. Been struggling a bit processing our conversations from last night/this morning. Mostly, I am sad that I haven’t been able to make you feel loved  and desired in the way I truly feel toward you. I’m wondering if we should consider getting some coaching/counseling to help us. We have been through so much change together the last two years, that I want to make sure we do everything we can to continue building a healthy, loving, intimate, and caring relationship. I am totally committed to go deeper, examine my own patterns/fears/wiring to gain some new insight and tools...to learn how to better speak your “love language.” I don’t know if I can do it on my own....Also, hearing how much you are trying to assimilate....with all of the changes you are trying to work through, getting some outside perspective could help. I love you so deeply and am so incredibly attracted to you...hearing you play back to me again that I’m deficient in showing this...and that you’ve basically written off and accepted this as just the way it is going to be.....feels to me like a failure for both of us.  I know this stuff is complex, and that there is another side...that you desire more attention, and that there may be some things at work here from your past that  you are ready to let go of. Some of your need for attention and  my inability to naturally give it may be our insecurities at play. As we say....both can be true. I do agree with you that we cannot be everything to each other, but we also haven’t fully explored what we can be for one another. And that is the journey with you to which I am fully committed. I feel like we’ve just scratched the surface....and we’ve been so consumed by high velocity external change, that a bit more focused self-reflection and relationship care could be in order to take us further. I love you more and more every day. I want you to feel and experience that every day....and I want to feel it too.', 'David', 'Nitzan', '2017-11-20T15:50:34'),
(5203, '76C86C90-4E3F-4457-AD70-054AC2A4C859', 'Thanks love for this note. It’s hard not to cry while reading it. This is all very emotional for me. And I know it is for you too. I do feel loved by you. And I feel like I’m in the most successful partnership I’ve ever been in by 100x. I feel understood and I feel like we partner well together in the world. I didn’t mean to write this part off. It’s just that we’ve talked about it before and then it dies down after a few weeks. So I know I’m working against your wiring. We can talk about whether we need counseling or whether we can work it through on our own. I’m open to both. ', 'Nitzan', 'David', '2017-11-20T16:05:02'),
